name: Dulce Crepes
directions: In back.

name: Kalle Bodega
directions: There are two gendered toilets and one toilet that is non gendered.
comment: Toilet is meant for customers (I guess)

name: Speedway
directions: Go directly back from front door, then turn right at specialty coffee machine
comment: Store should be open 24 hours.

name: Tramps Patio Bar
comment: You have to ask for the key

name: Brindles Ice Cream Shop
comment: Must be a customer.

name: Krispy Kreme Doughnuts
directions: Go thru the main entrance, and immediately to your right there are 2 stalls.
comment:
You need to get a key from the workers to access them.

The left stall doesn't have a changing table, but I'm not sure about the right stall.

name: Cherry Sushi Bar
directions: In the hallway next to the kitchens
comment: You do need to be a customer, but they have excellent sushi!

name: ABC Pizza
directions: In back on left
comment: Small friendly restaurant; will need to interact with owners, but will probably happily let you use the restroom.  There is a door to two single stall bathrooms, so chances are you will also have privacy in which one you go in.

name: The Roasted Garlic
comment: Friendly workers don't care which single stall bathroom you use.

name: Prep Kitchen Little Italy
directions: At the back of the resteraunt on the right side of the bar there are four gender neutral single stalls bordering a shared sink area (two single stalls on each side)
comment: Probably have to be a customer, could buy a great butterscotch muffin for -$3

name: Wal mart
directions: Back of stores next to pick up and photo desk.

name: Arctic Circle
directions: On the side of the building where the drive thru is.

name: Target
directions: Go to greeting cards, then turn towards the back of the store.  Restrooms are next to the refrigerated item. One of them is the family bathroom.

name: Starbucks (Clover Rd)
directions: In the back hallway

name: Spud Fish and Chips
directions: Head right once inside the front door
comment: Two single stall restrooms marked gender neutral, with a changing table in one restroom. The other has a urinal in addition to a toilet. Formerly gendered restrooms that have been updated with new signage.

name: Wendy's
directions: When you enter through the front you turn right and walk down a hallway. There are two single stall restrooms.

name: Pet Supplies Plus
directions: At the end of the first aisle right when you walk in the doors. Turn right right before fish tanks
comment: Act like you're browsing for a bit.

name: Homegrown
comment: May need to be paying customer

name: Ana's Taqueria
directions: To the left, in the back.
comment: There are two of them

name: Half Price Books
directions: Both bathrooms are now gender neutral

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Far left of the store, by the checkout lines

name: GameUnderground
directions: In the back of shop. Two bathrooms.
comment: You should spend a few dollars playing some arcade games anyways but lax staff and if you ask they'll tell you where exactly. Near American Doll Store

name: Oberon Theater
comment: Men and women's room made into 2 huge gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back

name: Barnes & Noble in Edina Galleria
directions: By registers
comment: I'm sure they expect you to be a paying customer but it's large and busy enough to sneak by.

name: Goodwill
directions: At the back-right corner of the store, behind the men's wear area
comment: Ask for the restroom key from cashier at cash area (front of store) before using the restroom

name: Galleria Edina
directions: Enter by Pittsburgh Blue. (There are probably others throughout the mall.)
comment: Multi-stall gendered bathrooms but also single stall family bathrooms.

name: Farmacia Gloriana
directions: By the front entrance by your right.

name: Avalon Bakery
directions: Both restrooms are the same
comment: Seem to be very clean as well

name: Planned Parenthood
comment: Available for health center patients.

name: Save On Foods
directions: In the back. Just ask for the bathroom
comment: It's chill just go straight back

name: The Elephant Walk
directions: Three single stall bathrooms. One gender-neutral, one women's, one men's

name: Fuddruckers
directions: Right behind the soda machines in dining area, separate from the gendered bathrooms.

name: Cafe Bernardo
directions: Hallway in the back, follow the signs to the right
comment: Prob have to be a paying customer but idk? Just get an iced tea or smth? Their pastries are p good too

name: Spirit Winds Coffee Bar
directions: Straight to the back unmarked but through a purple door frame there is a bathroom marked with an either/or for gender but it seems they do mean it is neutral.
comment: No paying customer necessity here, they will direct you where it is very kindly. Bathroom is very neat and clean for how much traffic they receive for the one restroom. Restroom has Febreeze!

name: Diabetes & Endocrinology Center of Ohio
directions: After going in, DECO is on the left.
comment: You have to ask the receptionist if you can use the restroom. They would probably prefer it be just for patients... but they have numerous trans patients and would probably be sympathetic if you explain You're trans and just need a unisex restroom.

name: Goodale Park
directions: There are porta potties in the middle of the park near the building.
comment: Personally I would suggest the unisex restroom at the Hilton, but this would work if it's an emergency.

name: University of Nebraska-Lincoln, Andrews Hall
directions: First floor, east side of the building, tucked away
comment: Might help to be affiliated with the university

name: Cassat's
comment: In the back. Notionally for customers, but directly accessible from the back door.

name: Video Game Rescue
directions: Through the hall on the right after walking in, go into the kitchen area straight ahead and take the first left. It's the only door.
comment: There's an old school arcade in the back, as well. You can use that as a cover.

name: Syntero
directions: Go in and turn right, then turn right again.
comment: This is a therapist/psychiatrist place. I imagine You're supposed to be a client but they won't say anything... and if they do, I imagine they'll be sympathetic if you explain You're trans and need to use the restroom.

name: Syntero
directions: Go inside, walk to the right hand side of the receptionist booth without even saying anything. Go all the way down the hallway on the right and turn right. You will pass the normal gendered restrooms, keep going. The hallway bends to the left a little but keep going straight. At the end of the hallway, turn left. When you get to the seating area there, turn left and the single-person unisex restroom will be on the left under the restroom sign.
comment: This is a therapist/psychiatrist place. I imagine You're supposed to be a client but they won't say anything... and if they do, I imagine they'll be sympathetic if you explain You're trans and need to use the restroom.

name: Divine Swine
directions: back on the right

name: Yogurtland
directions: In the very back
comment: You might have to ask for the key

name: Panera bread
directions: Towards the back
comment: You may need to ask the cashier for a key, but it seems that that is not in practice. There is urinal and a toilet.

name: The coffee bean & tea leaf
directions: Right when you walk in

name: Trolley Square Oyster House
directions: Second floor at the top of the steps

name: Schaefer's Canal House
directions: Bathroom serves the outdoor deck area. Walk just past the lighthouse bar and take a right. Bathroom is the first door on the side of the building.

name: The Outlets at Montehiedra - Caribbean Cinemas
directions: Within movie theatres.
comment:
Might need a movie ticket or you might ask to be allowed in. There are two single bathroom unisex bathrooms side by side.

Puedes que necesites comprar un boleto de película pero puedes pedir que te dejen usarlo. Hay dos baños unisex uno al lado del otro.

name: Hos Naboen
directions: Downstairs.
comment: Three closeted stalls marked unisex.

name: Next Door Bake Shop
directions: Back of the shop behind the kitchen.

name: Starbucks Stephens Green
street: Newman House, 18-21 Saint Stephen's Green, Dublin 2
directions: at the back just before the windows to and to your right, just past the area where the sugar and  everything is
comment: you usually have to be a paying customer but if you ask i'm sure it'll be okay

name: The Hub, University of the West of Scotland
directions: Follow the sign for the toilets, the unisex toilet is to the left once you reach the back corridor.
comment: This building is open to the public. You do not need to be a student to use this toilet.

name: Firefly Hollow Holistic Wellness
directions: First floor
comment: It's encouraged to be a customer

name: Peet's Coffee
comment: Two restrooms available. Both signs list as "All-Gender Restroom" with a white triangle. Braille listed below. Very open and accessible, extremely welcoming staff!

name: Kick Butt Coffee Music & Biize
directions: In the back. The code to get in is 2468.

name: Blackbird Salon
comment: Staff is incredibly inclusive and will let you go if you ask!

name: Bosco's
directions: Two single unisex restrooms; each has a toilet and a urinal
comment: Have to ask at the counter and they'll unlock it for you

name: Cava Olney
comment: the first restroom in the restroom area is gender neutral then there are also two gendered bathrooms

name: Bite Maplewood
directions: You'll see the door on the right when you walk in. The door leads to a hallway with a mirror and two rooms that each serve as a single stall bathroom.
comment: The owners are extremely friendly and will most likely let you use their restroom if you ask.

name: Serenity Garden Café
directions: There are two single stalls, both gender neutral, in the hallway of the indoor mall behind the café.

name: Hidden Treasures Thrift Store
comment: Looks kinda churchy in here, but if you look around a little, you should be fine

name: South Seas conference center
directions: Next to the tennis courts by main entrence
comment: If your at a confrence here, but acessable to public.

name: Clearwater travel plaza
directions: Through the main doors (coming from the gas pumps) and walk to the bakery and take a left. There's a single stall family restroom before the soda machine
comment: This location is always open 24/7, but it is quite busy during the daytimes!

name: La Montanita Co-op Food Market
directions: Sign says they don't gender their bathrooms because it makes people uncomfortable 👍

name: Cowgirl
directions: Go in past the bar and go right. Single room gender neutral bathroom.
